<subSubSection id="C309A2E9F36FFF94FF468CAFB722E609" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BACF162F36FFF94FF468CAFB722E609" blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1976]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="B9672D70F36FFF94FF468CAFB259E799" bold="true" box="[199,328,1230,1256]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C138AE1F36FFF94FED18CAFB121E799" authority="Rajan &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan &amp; Binoy, 2021" authorityName="Rajan &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan &amp; Binoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[336,560,1230,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Spilomena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsunekii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9672D70F36FFF94FED18CAFB121E799" box="[336,560,1230,1256]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Spilomena tsunekii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9672D70F36FFF94FDB98CAFB186E799" bold="true" box="[568,663,1230,1256]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A254900BF36FFF94FDB98CAFB186E799" box="[568,663,1230,1256]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from its congeners by the following combination of characters: frons and vertex imbricate, without setigerous micropunctures; mesopleuron finely aciculate, with illdefined punctures; relative length to breadth of scape = 20:5; stigma not elongate, relative length to breadth = 98:68; propodeal dorsum transversely striate, with two longitudinal carinae medially, posterior surface finely aciculate, with median longitudinal carina, lateral surface transversely striate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C309A2E9F36FFF95FF468DE3B2B3E428" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="272" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BACF162F36FFF94FF468DE3B725E6EC" blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1976]" box="[199,1076,1410,1437]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="B9672D70F36FFF94FF468DE3B271E6ED" bold="true" box="[199,352,1410,1436]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="54A84FC0F36FFF94FEE88DE3B2C6E6ED" box="[361,471,1410,1436]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount id="9D153AEBF36FFF94FE5F8DE2B2E6E6EC" box="[478,503,1411,1437]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
. Body length 
<quantity id="4CEB5C87F36FFF94FD1D8DE3B1EBE6EC" box="[668,762,1410,1437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.6 mm</quantity>
; fore wing length 
<quantity id="4CEB5C87F36FFF94FC538DE3B73EE6EC" box="[978,1071,1410,1437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BACF162F36FFF94FF468DC7B650E695" blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1976]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="B9672D70F36FFF94FF468DC7B232E6B0" bold="true" box="[199,291,1446,1473]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Colour.</emphasis>
Body black except pronotum yellowish brown; clypeus and metasoma brown; mandible (except apical tip brown), tegula, pronotal lobe, legs and antenna yellow; fore wing veins and stigma brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BACF162F36FFF94FF468D8FB618E579" blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1976]" box="[199,1289,1518,1545]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="B9672D70F36FFF94FF468D8FB22BE579" bold="true" box="[199,314,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Vestiture.</emphasis>
T5–T7 with scattered setigerous punctures; remaining body with sparse vestiture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BACF162F36FFF94FF468E73B62CE5E9" blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1976]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="B9672D70F36FFF94FF468E73B21EE55D" bold="true" box="[199,271,1554,1581]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="B9672D70F36FFF94FF468E73B216E55C" bold="true" box="[199,263,1554,1581]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Clypeus dull without any appressed setae, markedly convex (
<figureCitation id="1328EDE7F36FFF94FC7D8E73B747E55D" box="[1020,1110,1554,1580]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–44" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1664,1688]" captionTargetBox="[158,1419,187,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-104@10.[151,1424,181,1645]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 37–44. Spilomena tsunekii Tessy, Sureshan &amp; Girish Kumar, sp. nov., Holotype ♂. 37. Habitus, lateral view; 38. Head, frontal view; 39. Head and mesosoma (in part), dorsal view; 40. Mesosoma, lateral view; 41. Propodeum, dorsal view; 42. Metasoma, dorsal view; 43. Fore wing; 44. Hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704393/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
); interantennal tubercle inconspicuous, not distinctly pointed, extending into short median carina at most reaching lower frons; mandible bidentate, inner mandibular tooth short, blunt; relative length to breadth of scape =20:5 frons and vertex imbricate without setigerous micropunctures; inner eye margin straight; gena imbricate, impunctate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BACF162F36FFF94FF468EC2B1C3E4C9" blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1976]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="B9672D70F36FFF94FF468EC2B258E5CD" bold="true" box="[199,329,1698,1725]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="B9672D70F36FFF94FF468EC2B253E5CC" bold="true" box="[199,322,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Pronotum reticulate, with irregular longitudinal rugae; anterior carina of pronotal collar conspicuous, deeply emarginate; mesoscutum reticulate, with scattered setigerous punctures; admedian line and parapsidal line lacking; scutellum dull and reticulate, with sparse setigerous punctures, anterior groove of scutellum not broadened by crenulation; metanotum dull and reticulate, irregularly transversely rugose laterally; mesopleuron finely aciculate, with ill-defined punctures (
<figureCitation id="1328EDE7F36FFF94FDB88F53B19FE43D" box="[569,654,1842,1868]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–44" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1664,1688]" captionTargetBox="[158,1419,187,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-104@10.[151,1424,181,1645]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 37–44. Spilomena tsunekii Tessy, Sureshan &amp; Girish Kumar, sp. nov., Holotype ♂. 37. Habitus, lateral view; 38. Head, frontal view; 39. Head and mesosoma (in part), dorsal view; 40. Mesosoma, lateral view; 41. Propodeum, dorsal view; 42. Metasoma, dorsal view; 43. Fore wing; 44. Hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704393/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
); metapleuron finely aciculate; stigma not elongate, relative length to breadth = 98:68; recurrent vein of fore wing received well within first submarginal cell; propodeal dorsum transversely striate, with two longitudinal carinae medially, posterior surface finely aciculate, with median longitudinal carina (
<figureCitation id="1328EDE7F36FFF94FF6A8FFFB22FE4C9" box="[235,318,1950,1976]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–44" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1664,1688]" captionTargetBox="[158,1419,187,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-104@10.[151,1424,181,1645]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 37–44. Spilomena tsunekii Tessy, Sureshan &amp; Girish Kumar, sp. nov., Holotype ♂. 37. Habitus, lateral view; 38. Head, frontal view; 39. Head and mesosoma (in part), dorsal view; 40. Mesosoma, lateral view; 41. Propodeum, dorsal view; 42. Metasoma, dorsal view; 43. Fore wing; 44. Hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704393/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
), lateral surface transversely striate.
</paragraph>
